1
00:00:03,040 --> 00:00:04,400
You know you look beautiful today?

2
00:00:05,080 --> 00:00:06,280
What?

3
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:08,600
What’s this? Where’s this coming from all of a sudden?

4
00:00:08,680 --> 00:00:09,800
Just felt like telling you.

5
00:00:10,200 --> 00:00:12,280
Beautiful.
-Come on, stop.

6
00:00:12,360 --> 00:00:15,000
Girls, isn’t Mom beautiful today?
-Yeah.

7
00:00:15,440 --> 00:00:17,240
You’re the prettiest mom in your class.

8
00:00:18,120 --> 00:00:19,880
And you’re the prettiest girls in the world.

9
00:00:20,440 --> 00:00:22,520
Dad’s handsome too.
-Yeah, Dad’s handsome too.

10
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:23,440
Right.

11
00:00:23,520 --> 00:00:26,160
Even Grandma Riki?
-Yeah, Grandma Riki’s beautiful too.

12
00:00:26,320 --> 00:00:27,320
Tell me that today.

13
00:00:27,400 --> 00:00:29,360
Wait, sweetie,

14
00:00:29,440 --> 00:00:30,680
you’ll tell me that today,

15
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:34,240
but don’t say Mom told you
to say it, okay?

16
00:00:34,680 --> 00:00:35,840
Even if she asks.

17
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:38,680
You came up with that yourself.

18
00:00:38,760 --> 00:00:40,600
And don’t use the word “came up with.”

19
00:00:41,240 --> 00:00:44,080
You saw it yourself, okay?

20
00:00:44,560 --> 00:00:46,080
Sit down, what are you doing to the girl?
-What do you want?

21
00:00:46,160 --> 00:00:48,920
Sending her off to battle
without any basic training,

22
00:00:49,120 --> 00:00:50,120
it could ruin her life.

23
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:51,520
Okay, fine. I didn’t think.

24
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:53,520
I wanted her to get along with her mom,

25
00:00:54,200 --> 00:00:56,320
like your mom gets along with Itamar’s little one.

26
00:00:56,400 --> 00:00:58,480
No, they don’t get along.
-Oh, they get along just fine.

27
00:00:58,760 --> 00:01:01,360
That little one just reminds your mom
of how she was when she was little.

28
00:01:02,280 --> 00:01:03,480
I don’t think that’s a psychological reason,

29
00:01:03,960 --> 00:01:05,640
I think the little one just scares Mom.

30
00:01:05,720 --> 00:01:06,960
But they get along.

31
00:01:07,440 --> 00:01:08,920
Do you want to help Grandma?

32
00:01:09,640 --> 00:01:10,760
Do you want to draw?

33
00:01:11,560 --> 00:01:13,120
Do you want to stop yelling?

34
00:01:14,080 --> 00:01:16,080
Do you want to annoy Grandma?

35
00:01:17,440 --> 00:01:20,480
Exactly, and for that you deserve a prize,
cake with whipped cream.

36
00:01:21,760 --> 00:01:24,840
You’re going to eat it, whether you like it or not.

37
00:01:24,920 --> 00:01:26,840
I’m telling you, it just looks like they get along,

38
00:01:27,080 --> 00:01:28,280
something’s not right there.

39
00:01:28,360 --> 00:01:30,280
I don’t know, maybe because she’s Smadar’s daughter.

40
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:31,360
No, where?

41
00:01:31,440 --> 00:01:34,280
The girl is just as annoying
as Itamar was when he was a kid.

42
00:01:44,760 --> 00:01:46,880
At least our dads turned out great.
-Great.

43
00:01:46,960 --> 00:01:48,440
Great.
-Great.

44
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:53,160
Not a word of what you heard here to Grandma.

45
00:01:53,880 --> 00:01:54,720
Not a word.

46
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:02,800
Look at me, look at me and...

47
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:14,760
In short, I said it’s a disgrace
that half the city is walking around with a husband like hers.

48
00:02:15,320 --> 00:02:16,280
Seriously.
-Totally.

49
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:18,000
And he’s not even that great of a husband.

50
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:19,520
Not those, Pinchas, those are the destroyers.

51
00:02:19,720 --> 00:02:21,360
Oh, sure, yeah.

52
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:25,840
Did you?
-Did you put her to sleep? I don’t know, she got tired all of a sudden.

53
00:02:26,160 --> 00:02:28,200
I just hope she doesn’t stay awake all night now.

54
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:29,760
She’s with us.
-She’s with us.

55
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:31,240
Where’s the baby?
-I don’t remember anymore.

56
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:35,840
After you went to put the girl to bed
I found myself in a shoe store at the mall.

57
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:37,880
How much did that cost me, babe?

58
00:02:37,960 --> 00:02:39,080
Wait, so listen! Both of you.

59
00:02:39,160 --> 00:02:40,760
So she told me I was right,

60
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:44,480
and as compensation, I walked out of there with
two pairs of totally amazing shoes.

61
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:47,440
So how much did it cost me, babe?
-Nothing at all.

62
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:50,480
She gave them to me as a gift, for free, as compensation.

63
00:02:50,560 --> 00:02:52,480
Even the parking was on the company.

64
00:02:52,640 --> 00:02:55,520
Come on, babe, how nice, you bought something! For free.

65
00:02:55,640 --> 00:02:56,840
What, is this a historic moment?

66
00:02:56,920 --> 00:02:59,360
I'm so proud of you, babe.
-Thanks, babe.

67
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:00,560
I'm proud of myself too.

68
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:03,520
Just two weeks ago I bought
this outfit that I returned for some...

69
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:04,720
On sale.

70
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:06,000
I had a good week too,

71
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:08,240
I got an appointment with that doctor from Ramat Aviv,

72
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:12,000
And there's a good chance I'll go for a check-up next week.

73
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:13,360
That's great, Dad.

74
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:16,400
Anything specific?
-My red one came back.

75
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,640
They think it's nothing.

76
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:21,040
But other than that, everything's great.

77
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:23,760
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

78
00:03:23,840 --> 00:03:24,960
What's up? How's it going?

79
00:03:25,640 --> 00:03:27,560
What's new?
-Hey, girls.

80
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:31,640
We're all good, how about you?
-We're good, Dad.

81
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:33,800
Oh, Michal, those are beautiful shoes.
-Thanks.

82
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:34,720
I saw them at the mall,

83
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,960
Wow, that's 2500 shekels... on sale.
-On sale.

84
00:03:37,040 --> 00:03:39,320
And a big discount, it's buy one get one.

85
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:40,520
I'll talk to Riki for a sec.

86
00:03:42,520 --> 00:03:46,000
What... how's it going, Itamar?
-Fine, everything's great.

87
00:03:46,320 --> 00:03:48,760
How about you?
-Everything's great, great.

88
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:49,920
It's great on my end too.

89
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:53,760
Great.
-Well, if everyone’s great, great.

90
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:54,720
Great.
-Great.

91
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:58,680
You know that's not a belt, it's connected.

92
00:03:59,920 --> 00:04:00,880
Great.
-Great.

93
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:04,760
Hey, Riki.
-Hey, Shani.

94
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:08,840
Wow, what a nice shirt.
-Thanks.

95
00:04:09,160 --> 00:04:11,120
It looks lovely on you.
-Thanks.

96
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:13,080
What's up? What's new?

97
00:04:13,160 --> 00:04:14,600
Great.
-Yeah? What did you make?

98
00:04:15,480 --> 00:04:17,720
As usual, from my hit parade.

99
00:04:18,079 --> 00:04:19,720
Cool, everyone loves schnitzel and mashed potatoes.

100
00:04:20,320 --> 00:04:21,880
Wow, you're so quick, thanks a lot.

101
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:23,640
Babe, you’re exaggerating, I grew up with three sisters.

102
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:25,760
I eat
a lot
of beans.

103
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:27,960
So what's going on outside?
-Everything's great.

104
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:29,760
What a coincidence, just like in the living room.

105
00:04:30,280 --> 00:04:31,400
What are you talking about?
-Food.

106
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:32,320
Yeah.

107
00:04:32,520 --> 00:04:33,400
Don't worry, Michal,

108
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:37,200
I made you a green salad
and threw in some cranberries.

109
00:04:37,280 --> 00:04:38,800
Wow, that's great. Thanks, Riki.

110
00:04:38,880 --> 00:04:42,640
You know cranberries are good
for bladder infections, God forbid.

111
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:46,600
But I don’t have any.
-So for prevention, just in case,

112
00:04:46,760 --> 00:04:47,640
that way you don’t have to worry.

113
00:04:47,720 --> 00:04:49,240
Do I know where you’ve been hanging out?

114
00:04:49,320 --> 00:04:51,120
Riki.
-What?

115
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:54,480
Oh, sorry, Michal, I didn’t mean to,

116
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:57,600
that was out of context! And it was below the belt.

117
00:04:57,680 --> 00:04:59,480
That’s not even a belt, it’s connected.

118
00:05:01,840 --> 00:05:02,880
Connected to...

119
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:07,960
What a funny little thing, you’re killing me, you.

120
00:05:08,640 --> 00:05:10,760
You know I made a sabrina.
-Stop.

121
00:05:10,840 --> 00:05:13,560
No parts of dead animals.

122
00:05:13,640 --> 00:05:16,600
Wow, Sabreeva, what a joy.
-What joy?

123
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:18,400
A big joy.
-Wow.

124
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:19,920
Awesome.
-Awesome.

125
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:20,840
Awesome.

126
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:23,760
So, how's your health?

127
00:05:24,680 --> 00:05:27,280
Oh, you won't believe it, the red one I had
just went to Dad.

128
00:05:27,840 --> 00:05:30,080
What do you say? And you see
he’s not freaking out like you do when it happens to him.

129
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:32,640
I found the kids' dental numbing cream

130
00:05:32,840 --> 00:05:34,280
that one of you forgot at our place,

131
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:36,520
I applied it, and since then everything's been great.

132
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:37,520
Awesome.

133
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:40,720
Did you know that "Zabam" in Russian means "Zubi"?

134
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:42,320
Awesome.
-Awesome.

135
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:44,800
How's work, Itamar?

136
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:46,200
Totally fine.
-Yeah?

137
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:49,240
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

138
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:51,760
Adamka, great, Shalom to you too.
-Shalom.

139
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:53,440
What’s up, buddy...

140
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:57,120
Wait, I have... I have déjà vu.
Haven't you been here before?

141
00:05:57,200 --> 00:06:02,280
Yeah, aren’t you the one who checked my red one?
-Yeah, that’s not something you forget.

142
00:06:02,360 --> 00:06:05,360
Well, if I had a shekel for every time
someone said that to me...

143
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:06,840
So, would you have a shekel?

144
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:10,320
I, for sure, am the doctor.

145
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:12,040
What a coincidence,

146
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:15,640
next week I have an appointment for my red one,
maybe it’s for Ruby.

147
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:19,760
I’m not obligated to check it.
-It’s okay, you don’t have to, Tavasmi.

148
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:22,120
Guys, let’s all come together for a moment, okay?

149
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:24,040
Last time it was totally fine so...

150
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:25,360
Awesome.
-Awesome.

151
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:27,600
How nice, everything’s great, awesome.

152
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:29,360
Awesome.
-Awesome.

153
00:06:30,440 --> 00:06:32,320
Dad, my battery's dead.

154
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:34,960
No way.

155
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:36,160
Let me see.

156
00:06:39,080 --> 00:06:40,080
No, it’s dead.

157
00:06:40,160 --> 00:06:42,360
Okay, Raz, Raz, Raz, relax, relax,

158
00:06:42,440 --> 00:06:44,080
Tavasum, everything’s fine,
nothing happened, nothing happened,

159
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:46,120
Dad will take care of everything, it’s all good.
-Awesome.

160
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:47,600
Is that how his voice sounds?

161
00:06:47,680 --> 00:06:49,880
I don’t know, I haven’t heard him talk
for about three weeks.

162
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:54,800
Here’s the business card,
I know her personally.

163
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:57,480
"Mariva Meni Padi"?
-Yeah, she also does mustaches.

164
00:06:57,640 --> 00:06:58,600
What?

165
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:02,280
No, you don’t have a mustache,
she just says she does mustaches too.

166
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:06,480
Mom.
-What does he want? Why is he yelling like that?

167
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:09,080
If you want, she also does back and shoulders.

168
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:10,520
What?

169
00:07:11,960 --> 00:07:13,320
I don’t know, I didn’t get that either.

170
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:14,720
For Itamar.

171
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:16,520
Itamar...

172
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:19,240
Mom, Mom, you won’t believe it,
Raz's battery is dead.

173
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:21,280
What battery?
-The "PSP" one.

174
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:22,440
What’s a PSP?

175
00:07:22,520 --> 00:07:24,320
PSP, honey, only hearts have PSP.

176
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:27,880
PSP is his game,
it’s not good, you don’t understand?

177
00:07:27,960 --> 00:07:28,840
It can go downhill really fast.

178
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:32,960
Wait, Mom, did you maybe keep that game,
the Tetris I used to have?

179
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:35,160
It’s probably in one of the drawers.

180
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:37,360
You know I don’t throw anything away.

181
00:07:37,440 --> 00:07:41,200
Pinchas says it's a big deal.
Otherwise, I would have tossed him too.

182
00:07:42,840 --> 00:07:44,320
'Naf' top, all good, big love.

183
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:46,760
Come help me find it before
the kids here go out of control.

184
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:48,200
And all the fun everyone’s having will end.

185
00:07:48,280 --> 00:07:51,000
Okay, okay, why are you so hysterical?

186
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:54,320
Maybe you should come with us to the fun fair,
it’ll calm you down a bit.

187
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:57,160
In a fight.
-What's his deal, why is he so stressed?

188
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:58,080
I don’t know.

189
00:07:59,160 --> 00:08:00,720
But the truth is, now that I think about it,

190
00:08:00,840 --> 00:08:03,440
Whenever Raz is over, he’s glued
to those games of his.

191
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:04,880
Sometimes I totally forget he’s in the room.

192
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:06,280
Seriously.
-Yeah.

193
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:08,440
Once, Itamar and I had a huge fight, yelling and all,

194
00:08:08,520 --> 00:08:11,480
and then we wanted to, you know,
keep yelling and all,

195
00:08:11,880 --> 00:08:13,040
suddenly I realize Raz is in the room.

196
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:15,760
We moved to the service balcony, he didn’t even notice.

197
00:08:17,280 --> 00:08:18,280
Cool.

198
00:08:20,920 --> 00:08:22,000
So, what’s up, Raz?

199
00:08:22,080 --> 00:08:23,600
Other than the battery, everything’s great.
-Awesome.

200
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:26,680
Have you gained weight?
-What?

201
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:28,560
No, not really.

202
00:08:29,280 --> 00:08:31,560
Do you even remember us?

203
00:08:31,640 --> 00:08:34,440
Since when do you have a beard?
-Two weeks.

204
00:08:34,520 --> 00:08:35,520
It doesn’t suit you.

205
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:37,720
Is this your girlfriend?
-Yeah.

206
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:40,159
You’re tall.
-True.

207
00:08:40,240 --> 00:08:41,240
Originally from Adam.

208
00:08:42,159 --> 00:08:43,960
Good.
-So why are you dating him?

209
00:08:45,360 --> 00:08:47,280
What, doesn’t it bother you that people laugh at you behind your back?

210
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:50,440
When you laugh, your belly shakes.

211
00:08:51,560 --> 00:08:53,800
Raz, Raz, come here, you know what?

212
00:08:54,920 --> 00:08:57,200
Here, play a bit with my phone.
-Thanks.

213
00:08:58,200 --> 00:09:00,280
You have a really nice house.
-Thanks.

214
00:09:00,360 --> 00:09:03,680
Sorry for replying just now.
I’m free for you tonight,

215
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:06,200
whenever you want, just come already. A lot.

216
00:09:06,800 --> 00:09:08,840
What?
-That’s an SMS you just got.

217
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:10,200
And she sent a picture of herself.

218
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:13,760
She probably just woke up
because she’s not dressed yet.

219
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:19,320
That’s Dad’s underwear drawer.
Why is it even there?

220
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:21,920
So look in another drawer and don’t make a mess.

221
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:25,680
Why don’t you give him a book to read?
-I wish,

222
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:26,840
he doesn’t even know what a book is,

223
00:09:26,920 --> 00:09:29,000
give him a book, he’ll look for
the on and off button.

224
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:32,160
A book for them is just something
to throw at their sister when she annoys them.

225
00:09:32,520 --> 00:09:34,000
She was sitting.
-Come on, really.

226
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:38,480
Tell me, are you normal?
-Tell me, don’t you see she was sitting?

227
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:40,520
Tell me, are you normal?

228
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:43,400
Do you think if I were normal, I’d be
rummaging through Mom’s bra drawer?

229
00:09:44,920 --> 00:09:46,840
Okay, listen to me carefully,
you need to do something about your kid.

230
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:47,920
He’s not normal.

231
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:51,000
You know, when he was little and came here,

232
00:09:51,280 --> 00:09:54,440
I’d put headphones on him,
sit him in front of the TV,

233
00:09:55,040 --> 00:09:56,800
he’d sit there for hours.

234
00:09:57,400 --> 00:10:01,680
In the end, I’d give him a reward, chocolate.

235
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:03,960
Dude, that was predictable.
-Right?

236
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:06,240
And you still haven’t seen it coming.

237
00:10:08,520 --> 00:10:11,400
Come on, go wash up.
-I need to drink something.

238
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:14,560
Want me to pour you some water?
-Do you have something stronger?

239
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:16,200
Oh, yeah, sure.

240
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:18,640
What’s this?

241
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:20,320
Weird creator, everything's done.

242
