00:21:27,200 --> 00:21:28,520
Who?
-Mom.

481
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:31,000
Turns out she told us
what she thinks about each of us.

482
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:32,560
So just in case you get confused...

483
00:21:33,760 --> 00:21:35,200
Thanks, thanks, thanks.

484
00:21:35,280 --> 00:21:38,160
There are plenty of situations where I drink,
it’s not aimed at them.

485
00:21:38,800 --> 00:21:40,440
Like, I drink when I go out with friends,

486
00:21:40,560 --> 00:21:43,560
I drink after class, I drink
when I meet the girls for lunch,

487
00:21:43,800 --> 00:21:45,760
In the mornings, hardly ever.
-Sure, sure.

488
00:21:45,840 --> 00:21:47,240
Only on Saturdays.

489
00:21:47,320 --> 00:21:48,520
Wha...

490
00:21:49,160 --> 00:21:51,680
No problem at all.
-We talked about this earlier, right?

491
00:21:51,840 --> 00:21:52,760
Why are you surprised?

492
00:21:52,840 --> 00:21:55,680
I heard you talking
to your mom on the phone about the Rosen family.

493
00:21:55,880 --> 00:21:59,480
That’s not nice, I’m sure they
didn’t mean for us to hear that.

494
00:21:59,560 --> 00:22:02,960
Grandma is right.
-Not bad stuff, I hope.

495
00:22:03,040 --> 00:22:05,360
Are curses considered bad?
-Shai, can I?

496
00:22:05,840 --> 00:22:09,840
Hey, Raz, didn’t Grandma ever tell you
what she thinks about each of us?

497
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:11,480
Of course.
-Move, move.

498
00:22:12,160 --> 00:22:14,520
I bought this from some kid for 2,800 shekels down below.

499
00:22:15,280 --> 00:22:17,600
Wait, nothing, don’t talk now.

500
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:19,840
Here, Dad’s connecting, yeah.

501
00:22:20,040 --> 00:22:22,000
Here, please.

502
00:22:23,840 --> 00:22:26,320
This is great.
-Awesome.

503
00:22:27,120 --> 00:22:27,960
Should we go eat?

504
00:22:28,040 --> 00:22:31,320
You drank the leftovers earlier?
-Yeah.

505
00:22:31,560 --> 00:22:35,240
I have a feeling they need this.
-Cheers!

506
00:22:35,440 --> 00:22:36,600
Sh’, that’s a big problem.

507
00:22:37,160 --> 00:22:41,080
That’s a joke that got out of hand.
Okay, I got it, I’ll remember, it won’t happen again.

508
00:22:41,160 --> 00:22:42,160
Alright.

509
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:43,960
Everything’s good.

510
00:22:44,720 --> 00:22:45,800
You really look beautiful today.

511
00:22:46,560 --> 00:22:47,720
Wow.

512
00:22:47,800 --> 00:22:50,920
Adam’s girlfriend is prettier because you’re older.

513
00:22:53,120 --> 00:22:54,440
We need to buy her a PSP.

514
00:22:58,080 --> 00:23:00,120
A bimbo, huh? Great bimbo.

515
00:23:00,920 --> 00:23:03,560
Wow, how nice, sweet, sweet.

516
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:04,880
Sorry.

517
00:23:05,840 --> 00:23:07,680
When you laugh, your belly shakes.

518
00:23:08,360 --> 00:23:10,800
What?
-Raz, Raz, Raz, come...

519
00:23:17,040 --> 00:23:18,040
I’d be looking now

520
00:23:18,560 --> 00:23:20,840
in the underwear, for the bras...

521
00:23:24,160 --> 00:23:26,320
You have to do something about your son,
he’s not normal.

522
00:23:33,200 --> 00:23:34,440
Michal doesn’t agree with you.

523
00:23:36,240 --> 00:23:37,240
You know sometimes you have...

524
00:23:38,880 --> 00:23:41,160
Does it make you laugh that I got stuck?
-Me too.

525
00:23:42,240 --> 00:23:45,080
It doesn’t matter the size, the length...

